File: Five people have been sentenced to death for killing Saudi journalist, Jamal Khashoggi. JOHANNESBURG - Five people have been sentenced to death for killing Saudi journalist, Jamal Khashoggi. Three others received jail terms of 24-years each. A Saudi court dismissed charges against the remaining three of the 11 people that had been on trial. Khashoggi was an outspoken critic of Saudi Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman. WATCH: Body parts of slain journalist Jamal Khashoggi have been found He was last seen early in October at the Saudi consulate in Istanbul. The journalist's murder caused a global uproar.